BaseHTTP (HEAD unsupported, 501 response).\n- Backend servers (20.200.0.2–.4) behind the load balancer are also Python BaseHTTP servers (not Apache) and do not support HEAD. This propagates 501 responses through the load balancer.\n- Elevated total HTTP time (~1.0–1.2 s) for simple requests, inconsistent with low network RTTs, points to application-layer delay (not a routing or transport issue).\n\nFault localization\n- Web plane:\n  - Public-facing servers: web_server_0 (10.200.0.3), web_server_1 (10.200.0.4), web_server_2 (10.200.0.5), web_server_3 (10.200.0.6).\n  - Backend servers: 20.200.0.2/20.200.0.3/20.200.0.4 (referenced by the load balancer).\n  - Load balancer: load_balancer (10.200.0.7, 20.200.0.1) is healthy and correctly proxying to the configured upstreams.\n- Routing/DNS/DHCP plane: No faults detected. OSPF topology and advertisements are consistent; DNS is functional; backend isolation is enforced by routing.\n\nLikely root cause\n- The web servers (both public web_server_0..3 and backend 20.200.0.2–.4) are not running Apache as specified; instead they are running Python’s BaseHTTP server. This causes:\n  - Unsupported HTTP methods (HEAD returns 501).\n  - Likely noncompliance with intended application behavior and potentially added response delays observed in curl totals.\n- Network infrastructure (switching, IP connectivity, OSPF, DNS, DHCP) does not show evidence of defects contributing to the observed HTTP issues.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 46435, "output_tokens": 6384, "total_tokens": 52819, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 45440}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 4864}}}
